EXTRACTED VALUE: Sure, said my father, tapping a handful of mail against her back.
“Back?” Melissa said, her voice rising in volume, “Back? He’s never even seen her!”
It was a sentence she’d never said before.
Much unfortunate confusion is caused by failure to distinguish
different. She wasn't sore anywhere, and when she tossed back the bedclothes, holding her breath, there was no blood.
“He’s nobody,” replied Gavin through his sore, clenched jaw. “Just my neighbor.”
“Well, dammit,” I snapped. “If y’all ain’t hirin’, why didn’t ya just say so in the first place?”
How many times had he said that to me over the years? And yet now, when the crunch came for him, he wasn't truly ready to believe it himself.
